Depersonalization is rampant in today’s trying times, it’s behind so many emotional and mental struggles. Toxic Heavy Metals and chemical poisons found in fragrances, scented candles, air fresheners, laundry detergents, fabric softeners, dryer sheets, cologne, perfume, carpet chemicals, pharmaceuticals, mosquito spray, bug spray, and pesticides that are entering our bodies on a daily basis are greatly responsible 

Are you feeling like you are observing yourself from outside of your body and not from the inside? Feeling like you are in a bubble, like things around you aren’t real. Or feeling
like you are in a bubble cut off from outside world? 

Many people feel so disconnected from themselves and feel numb, not hearing what others are saying to them or feeling so displaced and even isolated while around others. 
 
Depersonalization can be a sadness we can’t put our finger on that sits inside us making us doubt ourselves and our purpose. So many struggle with confidence and feel confused. 

We can break free from depersonalization and empower ourselves and learn how to heal 

For more info check out the New York Times Bestselling book Cleanse to Heal

CURRY POCKETS {GLUTEN-FREE, DAIRY-FREE, & FAT-FREE}

These wonderfully hearty and flavorful Curry Pockets are the perfect meal or snack to satisfy you without weighing you down. Made with healing vegetables and spices, they are fat free, grain free, and plant based. Pair them with a green salad for a delicious dinner or lunch at home, or pack them into lunch boxes for your whole family to enjoy.

Curry Pockets

Potato pocket ingredients:

4-5 medium-sized potatoes 
1 tbsp potato starch
3 tbsp tapioca flour (more if needed)
Sea salt and pepper (optional)
1/2-1 tsp water (if needed)

Curry filling:

1 cup finely chopped cauliflower
1/3 cup frozen green peas, defrosted
1/4 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp ground cilantro
1/2 ground turmeric
1.5 tsp curry powder
Small handful fresh cilantro, finely chopped
Sea salt & pepper to taste (optional)
1 tsp lemon juice (optional)

Directions:

Place all the potatoes in a large pot fitted with a steaming basket. Add a few inches of water and steam until soft, about 45 minutes. Remove and cool for 10 to 15 minutes, until cool enough to handle. 

Place the potatoes in a large, flat-bottomed bowl or pot and mash until they are broken down. Add the salt, pepper, potato starch, tapioca flour and mash until the flour and starch have been incorporated. If the mixture is very dry, add a bit of warm water. If the mixture is very wet, add a bit more tapioca flour. The dough should be pliable and not stick to your fingers. Set aside while you make the filling.

Steam the chopped cauliflower in a steaming basket or fine mesh sieve over a pot of water until cooked. Remove and add to a bowl with the peas, ground cumin, ground cilantro, curry powder, fresh cilantro, sea salt, pepper and lemon juice (if using). Mix well. 

To make the pockets, take a handful of the potato mixture and roll it into a ball. Flatten the sides out so that there is a cavity in the middle, then add a tablespoon of the filling. Close the pocket gently and smooth out any creases. Repeat with remaining dough.
